{
  "name": "css-art",
  "title": "CSS Art",
  "description": "CSS is usually taught as a way to handle layout, color, and typography, but it can also be pushed much further. In CSS Art it becomes a medium for creative expression, less about the end result and more about honing your skills, discovering new techniques, and learning how to bend the language in creative ways. In this lesson, we’ll explore that experimental side of CSS and practice core techniques for turning simple code into artwork, leaving you with a template you can use as a starting point for your own CSS art.",
